{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782526525122,"sessionID":"ses_0f923eeffffeBaDzycyPMFxg4Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kl4dy9NdZny3LFBjF6sSooEE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","limit":400},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Platform Capability Check\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n6: \n7: ## Status Values\n8: \n9: `deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n10: \n11: ## Deferred Required Fields\n12: \n13: `targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n14: \n15: ## Entries\n16: \n17: | capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n18: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n19: | media-library-access | planned | phase-04-home-history | critical | needs-target-search |  | Media library and album discovery |  |  |\n20: | file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |\n21: | image-viewer-gestures | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | Image viewer gestures and metadata |  |  |\n22: | localization-resources | planned | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources | high | needs-target-search |  | Localized resources and formatted strings |  |  |\n23: | runtime-permissions | planned | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | needs-target-search |  | Runtime permissions and protected platform access |  |  |\n24: | background-and-platform-components | planned | phase-02-startup-session-navigation | high | needs-target-search |  | Background work, services, receivers, widgets, and notifications |  |  |\n\n(End of file - total 24 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Platform Capability Check\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis is the agent-maintained platform capability check. Before marking a critical/high platform capability as direct, replaced, fallback, or deferred, query CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie API docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, or package index lookup such as `https://pkg.cangjie-lang.cn` and record the evidence in `targetCapabilitySearch`. Direct means callable from the Cangjie target; ArkTS-only or native-only declarations are discovery evidence until an already planned or existing Cangjie wrapper, FFI, or bridge is verified with target build evidence. Use cjpm/project-management docs only to configure a chosen dependency.\n\n## Status Values\n\n`deferred`, `implemented-fallback`, `not-applicable`, `not-covered`, `planned`, `platform-replaced`, `unreviewed`, `verified-direct`\n\n## Deferred Required Fields\n\n`targetCapabilitySearch`, `blocker`, `targetFallback`, `futureCompletionPath`\n\n## Entries\n\n| capability id | status | phase | importance | decision | probe | capability | target API/library | strategy |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| media-library-access | planned | phase-04-home-history | critical | needs-target-search |  | Media library and album discovery |  |  |\n| file-access-and-saf | planned | phase-05-detail-cart | critical | needs-target-search |  | File access, document permissions, and share URIs |  |  |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.md","time":{"start":1782526525115,"end":1782526525121}},"id":"prt_f06dc3e8d001Gx4uSIMMf8QZLO","sessionID":"ses_0f923eeffffeBaDzycyPMFxg4Q","messageID":"msg_f06dc2d7700192wU8sQIW2WtJw"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782526525177,"sessionID":"ses_0f923eeffffeBaDzycyPMFxg4Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_rVwvMLBMLTTtrBxEbVc6DJiz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py","limit":400},"output":"<path>D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n2: \"\"\"Apply narrow, validated patches to agent-maintained coverage authorities.\"\"\"\n3: \n4: from __future__ import annotations\n5: \n6: import argparse\n7: import copy\n8: import json\n9: import re\n10: import sys\n11: from collections import Counter\n12: from dataclasses import dataclass\n13: from pathlib import Path\n14: from typing import Any\n15: \n16: if __package__ in (None, \"\"):\n17:     sys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2]))\n18:     from shared.common import HelpFormatter, expand_path, now_iso, write_json, write_text  # type: ignore\n19:     from shared.source_coverage.constants import (  # type: ignore\n20:         MATRIX_DEFERRED_REQUIRED_FIELDS,\n21:         MATRIX_IMPLEMENTED_STATUSES,\n22:         MATRIX_PARITY_LEVELS,\n23:         MATRIX_STATUSES,\n24:         PLATFORM_CAPABILITY_IMPLEMENTED_STATUSES,\n25:         PLATFORM_CAPABILITY_STATUSES,\n26:     )\n27:     from shared.source_coverage.facts import (  # type: ignore\n28:         CAPABILITY_FACTS_KEY,\n29:         COVERAGE_FACTS_KEY,\n30:         default_capability_facts,\n31:         default_coverage_facts,\n32:         validate_capability_facts,\n33:         validate_coverage_facts,\n34:     )\n35:     from shared.source_coverage.matrix import (  # type: ignore\n36:         MATRIX_AGENT_FIELDS,\n37:         coverage_target_endpoints,\n38:         coverage_verification_evidence_items,\n39:         effective_matrix_status,\n40:         has_source_behavior_evidence,\n41:         has_target_behavior_evidence,\n42:         matrix_entries_by_id,\n43:         parity_level,\n44:     )\n45:     from shared.source_coverage.platform import (  # type: ignore\n46:         capability_entries_by_id,\n47:         capability_target_endpoints,\n48:         effective_capability_status,\n49:         has_compile_probe_evidence,\n50:         has_direct_unavailable_blocker,\n51:         has_replacement_api_evidence,\n52:         platform_missing_deferred_fields,\n53:     )\n54:     from shared.source_coverage.render import (  # type: ignore\n55:         platform_capability_check_markdown,\n56:         source_coverage_matrix_markdown,\n57:     )\n58:     from shared.source_coverage.utils import has_text, has_text_or_list  # type: ignore\n59: else:\n60:     from ..common import HelpFormatter, expand_path, now_iso, write_json, write_text\n61:     from .constants import (\n62:         MATRIX_DEFERRED_REQUIRED_FIELDS,\n63:         MATRIX_IMPLEMENTED_STATUSES,\n64:         MATRIX_PARITY_LEVELS,\n65:         MATRIX_STATUSES,\n66:         PLATFORM_CAPABILITY_IMPLEMENTED_STATUSES,\n67:         PLATFORM_CAPABILITY_STATUSES,\n68:     )\n69:     from .facts import (\n70:         CAPABILITY_FACTS_KEY,\n71:         COVERAGE_FACTS_KEY,\n72:         default_capability_facts,\n73:         default_coverage_facts,\n74:         validate_capability_facts,\n75:         validate_coverage_facts,\n76:     )\n77:     from .matrix import (\n78:         MATRIX_AGENT_FIELDS,\n79:         coverage_target_endpoints,\n80:         coverage_verification_evidence_items,\n81:         effective_matrix_status,\n82:         has_source_behavior_evidence,\n83:         has_target_behavior_evidence,\n84:         matrix_entries_by_id,\n85:         parity_level,\n86:     )\n87:     from .platform import (\n88:         capability_entries_by_id,\n89:         capability_target_endpoints,\n90:         effective_capability_status,\n91:         has_compile_probe_evidence,\n92:         has_direct_unavailable_blocker,\n93:         has_replacement_api_evidence,\n94:         platform_missing_deferred_fields,\n95:     )\n96:     from .render import platform_capability_check_markdown, source_coverage_matrix_markdown\n97:     from .utils import has_text, has_text_or_list\n98: \n99: \n100: MATRIX_OBJECT_FIELDS = {COVERAGE_FACTS_KEY}\n101: MATRIX_LIST_FIELDS = {\"verificationEvidence\", \"targetEndpoints\", \"tests\"}\n102: MATRIX_TEXT_FIELDS = set(MATRIX_AGENT_FIELDS) - MATRIX_LIST_FIELDS - MATRIX_OBJECT_FIELDS\n103: MATRIX_UPDATE_FIELDS = set(MATRIX_AGENT_FIELDS)\n104: MATRIX_ADD_FIELDS = MATRIX_UPDATE_FIELDS | {\n105:     \"featureId\",\n106:     \"featureName\",\n107:     \"sourcePath\",\n108:     \"importance\",\n109:     \"category\",\n110:     \"riskTags\",\n111:     \"keyClasses\",\n112:     \"keyMethods\",\n113:     \"androidIds\",\n114:     \"dependencies\",\n115:     \"featurePoint\",\n116:     \"sourceEvidence\",\n117: }\n118: MATRIX_ADD_REQUIRED_FIELDS = {\"featureId\", \"featureName\", \"sourcePath\", \"importance\", \"sourceEvidence\"}\n119: MATRIX_REQUIRED_LIST_FIELDS = (\"verificationEvidence\", \"targetEndpoints\", \"tests\")\n120: MATRIX_REQUIRED_TEXT_FIELDS = (\n121:     \"plannedPhase\",\n122:     \"sourceBehavior\",\n123:     \"targetBehavior\",\n124:     \"notes\",\n125:     \"deferredReason\",\n126:     \"targetFallback\",\n127:     \"risk\",\n128:     \"futureCompletionPath\",\n129: )\n130: \n131: PLATFORM_OBJECT_FIELDS = {CAPABILITY_FACTS_KEY}\n132: PLATFORM_LIST_FIELDS = {\n133:     \"targetCapabilitySearch\",\n134:     \"targetEndpoints\",\n135:     \"tests\",\n136:     \"sdkDeclarationEvidence\",\n137:     \"cangjieCallableEvidence\",\n138:     \"discoveryOnlyEvidence\",\n139:     \"compileProbeEvidence\",\n140: }\n141: PLATFORM_TEXT_FIELDS = {\n142:     \"status\",\n143:     \"plannedPhase\",\n144:     \"targetApiOrLibrary\",\n145:     \"targetStrategy\",\n146:     \"preResolutionDecision\",\n147:     \"phaseCapabilityResolution\",\n148:     \"blocker\",\n149:     \"targetFallback\",\n150:     \"futureCompletionPath\",\n151:     \"notes\",\n152: }\n153: PLATFORM_UPDATE_FIELDS = PLATFORM_LIST_FIELDS | PLATFORM_TEXT_FIELDS | PLATFORM_OBJECT_FIELDS\n154: PLATFORM_ADD_FIELDS = PLATFORM_UPDATE_FIELDS | {\n155:     \"capabilityId\",\n156:     \"capabilityName\",\n157:     \"importance\",\n158:     \"sourcePaths\",\n159:     \"sourceEvidence\",\n160:     \"sourceEvidenceSummary\",\n161:     \"requiredTargetCapabilitySearch\",\n162:     \"targetStrategyHint\",\n163:     \"minimumParity\",\n164:     \"requiredTests\",\n165:     \"allowedDeferredReasons\",\n166: }\n167: PLATFORM_ADD_REQUIRED_FIELDS = {\"capabilityId\", \"capabilityName\", \"importance\", \"sourceEvidenceSummary\"}\n168: \n169: \n170: class PatchError(ValueError):\n171:     \"\"\"Raised for user-facing patch validation errors.\"\"\"\n172: \n173: \n174: @dataclass(frozen=True)\n175: class PatchContext:\n176:     target_project: Path | None = None\n177:     legal_phases: frozenset[str] | None = None\n178:     allow_missing_endpoints: bool = False\n179:     allow_unknown_phase: bool = False\n180: \n181: \n182: def parse_args() -> argparse.Namespace:\n183:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n184:         description=(\n185:             \"Apply a strict JSON patch payload to source-coverage-matrix.json or \"\n186:             \"platform-capability-check.json and optionally sync the Markdown view.\"\n187:         ),\n188:         formatter_class=HelpFormatter,\n189:     )\n190:     parser.add_argument(\n191:         \"--kind\",\n192:         choices=(\"auto\", \"matrix\", \"platform\"),\n193:         default=\"auto\",\n194:         help=\"Authority type. auto infers from the authority filename.\",\n195:     )\n196:     parser.add_argument(\"--authority\", required=True, help=\"Authority JSON path to patch.\")\n197:     parser.add_argument(\n198:         \"--patch\",\n199:         default=\"\",\n200:         help=\"Strict JSON patch payload. Omit with --validate-only to just validate the authority.\",\n201:     )\n202:     parser.add_argument(\"--validate-only\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Validate the authority without applying a patch.\")\n203:     parser.add_argument(\"--dry-run\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Validate and summarize without writing files.\")\n204:     parser.add_argument(\n205:         \"--markdown\",\n206:         default=\"\",\n207:         help=\"Markdown mirror path. Defaults to the authority path with .md suffix.\",\n208:     )\n209:     parser.add_argument(\"--no-markdown\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Do not sync the Markdown mirror.\")\n210:     parser.add_argument(\"--summary-json\", default=\"\", help=\"Optional path for a machine-readable patch summary.\")\n211:     parser.add_argument(\n212:         \"--max-markdown-files\",\n213:         type=int,\n214:         default=250,\n215:         help=\"Maximum rows rendered in the Markdown mirror.\",\n216:     )\n217:     parser.add_argument(\n218:         \"--target-project\",\n219:         default=\"\",\n220:         help=(\n221:             \"Optional target project root. When set, targetEndpoints touched by this patch must point \"\n222:             \"to existing target files, with optional ::symbol checks.\"\n223:         ),\n224:     )\n225:     parser.add_argument(\n226:         \"--plan-json\",\n227:         default=\"\",\n228:         help=\"Optional strict plan.json. When set, plannedPhase values touched by this patch must exist in phases[].\",\n229:     )\n230:     parser.add_argument(\n231:         \"--allow-missing-endpoints\",\n232:         action=\"store_true\",\n233:         help=\"Skip targetEndpoints filesystem/symbol validation even when --target-project is set.\",\n234:     )\n235:     parser.add_argument(\n236:         \"--allow-unknown-phase\",\n237:         action=\"store_true\",\n238:         help=\"Skip plannedPhase validation even when --plan-json is set.\",\n239:     )\n240:     return parser.parse_args()\n241: \n242: \n243: def load_strict_json(path: Path, label: str) -> Any:\n244:     try:\n245:         return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n246:     except FileNotFoundError as exc:\n247:         raise PatchError(f\"{label} does not exist: {path}\") from exc\n248:     except json.JSONDecodeError as exc:\n249:         raise PatchError(f\"{label} is not strict JSON: {exc}\") from exc\n250:     except OSError as exc:\n251:         raise PatchError(f\"Could not read {label}: {exc}\") from exc\n252: \n253: \n254: def phase_label(raw: str) -> str:\n255:     value = str(raw).strip()\n256:     if not value:\n257:         return \"\"\n258:     if value.isdigit():\n259:         return f\"phase-{int(value):02d}\"\n260:     return value\n261: \n262: \n263: def phases_from_plan_data(data: Any) -> list[str]:\n264:     if not isinstance(data, dict):\n265:         return []\n266:     phases = data.get(\"phases\")\n267:     if not isinstance(phases, list):\n268:         return []\n269:     found: list[str] = []\n270:     for item in phases:\n271:         candidate = \"\"\n272:         if isinstance(item, dict):\n273:             candidate = str(item.get(\"id\") or item.get(\"name\") or item.get(\"phase\") or \"\").strip()\n274:         elif isinstance(item, str):\n275:             candidate = item.strip()\n276:         labeled = phase_label(candidate)\n277:         if labeled:\n278:             found.append(labeled)\n279:     return list(dict.fromkeys(found))\n280: \n281: \n282: def patch_context_from_args(args: argparse.Namespace) -> PatchContext:\n283:     target_project = expand_path(args.target_project) if args.target_project else None\n284:     if target_project is not None and not target_project.exists():\n285:         raise PatchError(f\"target project does not exist: {target_project}\")\n286:     if target_project is not None and not target_project.is_dir():\n287:         raise PatchError(f\"target project is not a directory: {target_project}\")\n288: \n289:     legal_phases: frozenset[str] | None = None\n290:     if args.plan_json and not args.allow_unknown_phase:\n291:         plan_path = expand_path(args.plan_json)\n292:         if plan_path is None:\n293:             raise PatchError(\"--plan-json was provided but did not resolve to a path.\")\n294:         plan_data = load_strict_json(plan_path, \"plan json\")\n295:         phases = phases_from_plan_data(plan_data)\n296:         if not phases:\n297:             raise PatchError(f\"plan json does not define a non-empty top-level phases array: {plan_path}\")\n298:         legal_phases = frozenset(phases)\n299: \n300:     return PatchContext(\n301:         target_project=target_project,\n302:         legal_phases=legal_phases,\n303:         allow_missing_endpoints=bool(args.allow_missing_endpoints),\n304:         allow_unknown_phase=bool(args.allow_unknown_phase),\n305:     )\n306: \n307: \n308: def infer_kind(kind: str, authority: Path) -> str:\n309:     if kind != \"auto\":\n310:         return kind\n311:     name = authority.name\n312:     if name == \"source-coverage-matrix.json\":\n313:         return \"matrix\"\n314:     if name == \"platform-capability-check.json\":\n315:         return \"platform\"\n316:     raise PatchError(\n317:         \"Could not infer authority kind from filename. Pass --kind matrix or --kind platform explicitly.\"\n318:     )\n319: \n320: \n321: def entry_id_field(kind: str) -> str:\n322:     return \"featureId\" if kind == \"matrix\" else \"capabilityId\"\n323: \n324: \n325: def entries_by_id(kind: str, authority: dict[str, Any]) -> tuple[dict[str, dict[str, Any]], list[str]]:\n326:     return matrix_entries_by_id(authority) if kind == \"matrix\" else capability_entries_by_id(authority)\n327: \n328: \n329: def status_counts(kind: str, authority: dict[str, Any]) -> Counter[str]:\n330:     counts: Counter[str] = Counter()\n331:     for entry in authority.get(\"entries\", []):\n332:         if not isinstance(entry, dict):\n333:             continue\n334:         if kind == \"matrix\":\n335:             status = effective_matrix_status(entry)\n336:         else:\n337:             status = effective_capability_status(entry)\n338:         counts[status] += 1\n339:     return counts\n340: \n341: \n342: def validate_authority_shape(kind: str, authority: Any) -> dict[str, dict[str, Any]]:\n343:     if not isinstance(authority, dict):\n344:         raise PatchError(\"Authority JSON must be an object.\")\n345:     entries = authority.get(\"entries\")\n346:     if not isinstance(entries, list):\n347:         raise PatchError(\"Authority JSON must contain an `entries` list.\")\n348:     id_field = entry_id_field(kind)\n349:     missing_ids = [\n350:         str(index)\n351:         for index, entry in enumerate(entries, start=1)\n352:         if not isinstance(entry, dict) or not str(entry.get(id_field) or \"\").strip()\n353:     ]\n354:     if missing_ids:\n355:         raise PatchError(f\"Authority has entries without explicit `{id_field}` at positions: {', '.join(missing_ids[:20])}.\")\n356:     by_id, problems = entries_by_id(kind, authority)\n357:     if problems:\n358:         raise PatchError(\"Authority structural problem(s): \" + \"; \".join(problems[:20]))\n359:     return by_id\n360: \n361: \n362: def split_target_endpoint(endpoint: str) -> tuple[str, str]:\n363:     raw_path, sep, raw_symbol = endpoint.partition(\"::\")\n364:     endpoint_path = raw_path.strip().strip(\"`\")\n365:     symbol = raw_symbol.strip().strip(\"`\") if sep else \"\"\n366:     # Accept common line suffixes such as foo.cj:42 without treating the line\n367:     # number as part of the path.\n368:     endpoint_path = re.sub(r\"(\\.(?:cj|json|ets|ts|js|xml|toml|yaml|yml|md|txt)):\\d+$\", r\"\\1\", endpoint_path)\n369:     return endpoint_path, symbol\n370: \n371: \n372: def endpoint_file_path(target_project: Path, endpoint_path: str) -> Path:\n373:     normalized = endpoint_path.replace(\"\\\\\", \"/\")\n374:     candidate = Path(normalized)\n375:     if candidate.is_absolute():\n376:         return candidate\n377:     return target_project / candidate\n378: \n379: \n380: def symbol_tokens(symbol: str) -> list[str]:\n381:     return [\n382:         token\n383:         for token in re.split(r\"[^A-Za-z0-9_]+\", symbol)\n384:         if token and token not in {\"self\", \"this\", \"prototype\"}\n385:     ]\n386: \n387: \n388: def validate_target_endpoint(target_project: Path, endpoint: Any) -> list[str]:\n389:     if not isinstance(endpoint, str) or not endpoint.strip():\n390:         return [\"targetEndpoint values must be non-empty strings\"]\n391:     endpoint_path, symbol = split_target_endpoint(endpoint)\n392:     if not endpoint_path:\n393:         return [f\"targetEndpoint `{endpoint}` is missing a target file path\"]\n394:     path = endpoint_file_path(target_project, endpoint_path)\n395:     if not path.exists():\n396:         return [f\"targetEndpoint `{endpoint}` file does not exist: {path}\"]\n397:     if not path.is_file():\n398:         return [f\"targetEndpoint `{endpoint}` is not a file: {path}\"]\n399:     tokens = symbol_tokens(symbol)\n400:     if tokens:\n\n(Showing lines 1-400 of 973. Use offset=401 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Apply narrow, validated patches to agent-maintained coverage authorities.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport copy\nimport json\nimport re\nimport sys\nfrom collections import Counter\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nif __package__ in (None, \"\"):\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).resolve().parents[2]))\n    from shared.common import HelpFormatter, expand_path, now_iso, write_json, write_text  # type: ignore\n    from shared.source_coverage.constants import (  # type: ignore\n        MATRIX_DEFERRED_REQUIRED_FIELDS,","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"..\\..\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py","time":{"start":1782526525171,"end":1782526525176}},"id":"prt_f06dc3ebd001F9b7WRzWdb4nHW","sessionID":"ses_0f923eeffffeBaDzycyPMFxg4Q","messageID":"msg_f06dc2d7700192wU8sQIW2WtJw"}}
